Technical assistance and capacity-building for Yemen in the field of human rights
1007. At the 39th meeting, on 25 September 2014, the representatives of the Netherlands and Yemen introduced draft resolution A/HRC/27/L.9/Rev.1, sponsored by the Netherlands and Yemen and co-sponsored by Australia, Austria, Bahrain, Bulgaria, Canada, Croatia, Cyprus, the Czech Republic, Denmark, Djibouti, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Indonesia, Iraq, Ireland, Italy, Japan, Jordan, Latvia, Lebanon, Libya, Luxembourg, Malta, Mauritania, Montenegro, New Zealand, Norway, Oman, Poland, Portugal, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Slovakia, Somalia, Spain, the State of Palestine, Sweden, Tunisia, Turkey, the United Arab Emirates, the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland and the United States of America. Subsequently, Belgium, Estonia, Ethiopia, Finland, Lithuania, Maldives, Morocco, the Republic of Korea, Romania, Slovenia, Switzerland and Thailand joined the sponsors.
1008. At the same meeting, the draft resolution was adopted without a vote (resolution 27/19).
Technical assistance and capacity-building for Yemen in the field of human rights
